
Argumentul 12
The Blind Spot That Has Been Hiding in Plain Sight

For years, people believed prophylaxis was about adding measures — more rules, more steps, more obligations.
But the real breakthrough doesn’t come from adding.
It comes from seeing what was always there, but never named.

The blind spot is simple:
most problems don’t come from what you fail to do, but from the environment that makes good choices impossible.
You don’t fix chaos with willpower.
You fix it by removing the frictions that generate chaos in the first place.
And once you see this, you can’t unsee it.
It’s the moment when prophylaxis stops being a checklist and becomes architecture.
Not “do this, do that”, but “build the space where the right things happen naturally”.

This is the shift that changes everything.
The shift from effort to design.
From discipline to clarity.
From struggle to flow.

It’s the blind spot that was hiding in plain sight —
and the moment you name it, the entire lesson takes a new shape.

